{"seq": 862, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-426", "record": {"id": "REQ-426", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Benchmark harness completion token budget must allow reasoning models to produce tool calls", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-426", "version": 1, "title": "Benchmark harness completion token budget must allow reasoning models to produce tool calls", "description": "max_completion_tokens must be at least 32768 for gpt-5.x and o-series models to prevent reasoning token exhaustion truncating tool call output", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-436"]}}, "prev_hash": "bfcaa77be74682ccf01ce0f89b81163aebc9f6f75e019fe4d637087db3142aa9", "hash": "dfc85febeae43bffc6de340b6ad8247369cb0e64f1982f27d81518f189b02a27", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 863, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-427", "record": {"id": "REQ-427", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "GovernanceBench metrics/report statistical and leaderboard outputs", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-427", "version": 1, "title": "GovernanceBench metrics/report statistical and leaderboard outputs", "description": "GovernanceBench metrics/report shall compute Wilson pass-rate confidence intervals, bootstrap cost-of-pass confidence intervals, first-pass and consistency statistics, scaffold-lift vs UNGOVERNED, model-tier mapping, democratization and Pareto summaries, and Hugging Face leaderboard JSON/rendered report sections.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-437", "TEST-438", "TEST-440", "TEST-441"]}}, "prev_hash": "dfc85febeae43bffc6de340b6ad8247369cb0e64f1982f27d81518f189b02a27", "hash": "879d9c23e8f142645e6394176e4e782e07eafb0859239c35d0d3eec66d7d3d53", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 864, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-428", "record": {"id": "REQ-428", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "gitignore normalizer must enforce disjoint allow/deny policy and untrack diverged paths", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-428", "version": 1, "title": "gitignore normalizer must enforce disjoint allow/deny policy and untrack diverged paths", "description": "normalize_esdb_gitignore_policy in sync.py must (a) separate tracked paths from ignored paths in two disjoint sets, (b) never emit a bare ignore rule for a path it also allows, (c) run git rm --cached for any deny-listed path found in git ls-files, and (d) make esdb_migration_manifest.json explicitly tracked", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-439"]}}, "prev_hash": "879d9c23e8f142645e6394176e4e782e07eafb0859239c35d0d3eec66d7d3d53", "hash": "9e1ef109b44c90b4389af835582be4f5f90ec01df4e93aa86dad2126dddf8d0b", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 865, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-429", "record": {"id": "REQ-429", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "checkpoint ESDB field must reflect active backend: show SQLite record count and chain status when chronomemory is unavailable, ChronoMemory count otherwise, and N/A when no ESDB is present", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-429", "version": 1, "title": "checkpoint ESDB field must reflect active backend: show SQLite record count and chain status when chronomemory is unavailable, ChronoMemory count otherwise, and N/A when no ESDB is present", "description": "The 'specsmith checkpoint' GOVERNANCE ANCHOR box must accurately show the active ESDB backend. When chronomemory (commercial) is the active backend and WAL exists, show record count and chain validity as now. When SQLite is the active backend (chronomemory absent or WAL missing), show 'SQLite (N recs, ✓ chain)' with actual SqliteStore record count and chain_valid() result. When no ESDB is present at all, show 'N/A'. The current 0-record default is misleading for SQLite-only installations.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-442"]}}, "prev_hash": "9e1ef109b44c90b4389af835582be4f5f90ec01df4e93aa86dad2126dddf8d0b", "hash": "68e4fc7ae17ae01baff294466af92c9128beb99790cf973262e35db6b070cad9", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 866, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-430", "record": {"id": "REQ-430", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "preflight release classifier must distinguish release execution from release tooling edits", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-430", "version": 1, "title": "preflight release classifier must distinguish release execution from release tooling edits", "description": "The deterministic broker must not classify edits to release.yml, packaging scripts, dist files, and release documentation as intent=release. Only utterances that explicitly execute a release (cut, publish, ship, tag vX.Y.Z, bump version) should trigger the release gate. Maintenance of release tooling must fall through to CHANGE classification so it can be accepted by scope-matching.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-443", "TEST-445"]}}, "prev_hash": "68e4fc7ae17ae01baff294466af92c9128beb99790cf973262e35db6b070cad9", "hash": "90ef99175aededdf9b2dbbbff20d23463dce5ee64973226fa1f631172dd74586", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 867, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-431", "record": {"id": "REQ-431", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "preflight release intent must accept when known scope matched or explicit REQ cited, and always allocate a work item", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-431", "version": 1, "title": "preflight release intent must accept when known scope matched or explicit REQ cited, and always allocate a work item", "description": "When intent=release is classified: (a) if the utterance contains explicit release-management REQ IDs (e.g. REQ-050, REQ-051) or the scope confidence >= 0.6, the decision must be accepted as a governed change; (b) needs_clarification must still allocate a work_item_id so specsmith approve --work-item can proceed; (c) the instruction must reference --req flag for explicit override. The current dead-end (needs_clarification + empty work_item_id) makes approve impossible.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-444"]}}, "prev_hash": "90ef99175aededdf9b2dbbbff20d23463dce5ee64973226fa1f631172dd74586", "hash": "d8e9127977d550e31dc5281dc705bf7c44c677ccbca8b19a78a23a6e2de73594", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 868, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-432", "record": {"id": "REQ-432", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "audit must flag empty or fallback-only governance YAML rule sets", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-432", "version": 1, "title": "audit must flag empty or fallback-only governance YAML rule sets", "description": "check_governance_yaml_content must iterate .specsmith/governance/*.yaml; fail audit if any file has rules: [] or rules: [{note: ...}] only. Gate on presence of governance dir. m001 silent-skip when source_md missing must become a loud warning.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-446", "TEST-452"]}}, "prev_hash": "d8e9127977d550e31dc5281dc705bf7c44c677ccbca8b19a78a23a6e2de73594", "hash": "d51062d7268064216c86bd7e80e743e0cf12094e9e9c698c4f85be162ffe0f3a", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 869, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-433", "record": {"id": "REQ-433", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "sync must warn when REQUIREMENTS.md contains REQ IDs absent from docs/requirements YAML files", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-433", "version": 1, "title": "sync must warn when REQUIREMENTS.md contains REQ IDs absent from docs/requirements YAML files", "description": "In YAML-first mode run_sync must compare IDs in docs/REQUIREMENTS.md against those loaded from docs/requirements/*.yml; emit SyncWarning for any ID present in markdown but absent from YAML with hint to add to yml and re-run sync. Same pattern for TESTS.md vs docs/tests/*.yml.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-447", "TEST-448"]}}, "prev_hash": "d51062d7268064216c86bd7e80e743e0cf12094e9e9c698c4f85be162ffe0f3a", "hash": "9cb5c9436349a83667e1b271fd4a0f92f01215bc38522c0a172af462364628c8", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 870, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:01Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-434", "record": {"id": "REQ-434", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "CLI verify_cmd must wire equilibrium to WI mark_implemented and files_touched", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-434", "version": 1, "title": "CLI verify_cmd must wire equilibrium to WI mark_implemented and files_touched", "description": "verify_cmd (cli.py) computes equilibrium but never calls WorkItemStore.mark_implemented or sets files_touched on the WI, unlike governance_logic.run_verify. verify_cmd must call run_verify from governance_logic or mirror the WI-update logic so WI status advances to implemented on equilibrium.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-449"]}}, "prev_hash": "9cb5c9436349a83667e1b271fd4a0f92f01215bc38522c0a172af462364628c8", "hash": "295114dad1f5287329823dca22c5a75e36b39bf36dd59d5f13cf33feb78a4362", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 871, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-435", "record": {"id": "REQ-435", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "infer_scope must apply a minimum relevance score threshold to drop incidental matches", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-435", "version": 1, "title": "infer_scope must apply a minimum relevance score threshold to drop incidental matches", "description": "infer_scope currently returns up to top_k=3 results with no minimum score floor (only overlap>0). Add min_score=0.15 parameter; filter out matches below threshold before returning. Update run_preflight to pass min_score=0.15 so only genuinely related requirements are associated with work items.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-450"]}}, "prev_hash": "295114dad1f5287329823dca22c5a75e36b39bf36dd59d5f13cf33feb78a4362", "hash": "e2e6dfe8824bae5663b49486b275d7785fcf98b1661f898bcc22ae25255b74ef", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 872, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-436", "record": {"id": "REQ-436", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "session_metrics.jsonl must record real token counts, cost, model, and work_item_id per turn", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-436", "version": 1, "title": "session_metrics.jsonl must record real token counts, cost, model, and work_item_id per turn", "description": "session_metrics.jsonl auto-save path passes only command=save with all telemetry defaults zero. Real per-turn token usage is captured in ESDB token_metric via write_token_metric (runner.py:614). Add flush_session_metrics helper that reads the most recent ESDB token_metric record and appends a populated MetricsRecord to session_metrics.jsonl after write_token_metric is called.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-451"]}}, "prev_hash": "e2e6dfe8824bae5663b49486b275d7785fcf98b1661f898bcc22ae25255b74ef", "hash": "d12885082173a13a7c4abd34920590decdbaf6a404770724c62067aaa544002f", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 873, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-437", "record": {"id": "REQ-437", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Datasource adapters must define retrieval contracts, resilience behavior, and citation normalization guarantees", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-437", "version": 1, "title": "Datasource adapters must define retrieval contracts, resilience behavior, and citation normalization guarantees", "description": "The datasources module (src/specsmith/datasources/) provides patent, publication, and citation adapters. Each adapter must declare a typed retrieval contract, handle transient failures with retry/backoff, and normalize citation output to a canonical schema. Absence of these guarantees makes adapter output unpredictable for governance evidence packs.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-453"]}}, "prev_hash": "d12885082173a13a7c4abd34920590decdbaf6a404770724c62067aaa544002f", "hash": "d5024af9e607001c84056d66adea673882a5cb7dbf2c73be7123a0f12df945da", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 874, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-438", "record": {"id": "REQ-438", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "GUI commands and views must provide governed parity with core CLI state and error semantics", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-438", "version": 1, "title": "GUI commands and views must provide governed parity with core CLI state and error semantics", "description": "The GUI surface (src/specsmith/gui/) exposes governance state visually. Every GUI action that maps to a CLI command must produce identical governance outcomes (preflight, audit, sync). GUI error messages must be derived from the same error taxonomy as the CLI. No silent failures.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-454"]}}, "prev_hash": "d5024af9e607001c84056d66adea673882a5cb7dbf2c73be7123a0f12df945da", "hash": "12162351d610e4226c6b7edb9cb8cd8955693e64c0de094fdb63d1b5013d59b4", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 875, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-439", "record": {"id": "REQ-439", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "IDE integration adapters must implement a uniform capability and error-handling contract", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-439", "version": 1, "title": "IDE integration adapters must implement a uniform capability and error-handling contract", "description": "Integration adapters (src/specsmith/integrations/: aider, copilot, cursor, gemini, windsurf, claude) must each declare supported operations, degrade gracefully when the target tool is unavailable, and surface errors through specsmith governance events rather than silent fallbacks.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-455"]}}, "prev_hash": "12162351d610e4226c6b7edb9cb8cd8955693e64c0de094fdb63d1b5013d59b4", "hash": "0e3924e7e45a1a93217955c816db790bcd24d61d99b6120e9a8c72e7e684ebe4", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 876, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-440", "record": {"id": "REQ-440", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Plugin management must define install, list, remove, and compatibility validation requirements", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-440", "version": 1, "title": "Plugin management must define install, list, remove, and compatibility validation requirements", "description": "The plugin lifecycle (specsmith plugin command + src/specsmith/plugins.py) must: enumerate installed plugins (list), validate manifests on install, reject incompatible plugin versions, and support removal without leaving orphaned state. Plugin errors must not propagate to core governance commands.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-456"]}}, "prev_hash": "0e3924e7e45a1a93217955c816db790bcd24d61d99b6120e9a8c72e7e684ebe4", "hash": "201c4569d2aa6bcd515fee7a2f1169fe299a4dfe5754472621f0d99416eaf710", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 877, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-441", "record": {"id": "REQ-441", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "specsmith plugin CLI must document and enforce plugin command surface (list, validate, install, remove)", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-441", "version": 1, "title": "specsmith plugin CLI must document and enforce plugin command surface (list, validate, install, remove)", "description": "The specsmith plugin command is a CLI surface with no explicit REQ. It must: list all installed entry-point and manifest plugins (plugin list), validate plugin manifests before activation (plugin validate), and provide clear error messages when plugins fail to load.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-457"]}}, "prev_hash": "201c4569d2aa6bcd515fee7a2f1169fe299a4dfe5754472621f0d99416eaf710", "hash": "21d8cc8e987af83c11d562cec0314eee8e6d843d79844eaf26c7fd146c5e4030", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 878, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-442", "record": {"id": "REQ-442", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "specsmith pr CLI must cover governed pull request creation, status, and merge workflows", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-442", "version": 1, "title": "specsmith pr CLI must cover governed pull request creation, status, and merge workflows", "description": "The specsmith pr (create-pr/governed-pr) command surface has no explicit REQ. It must: create PRs with governance comment blocks, evaluate PR governance status against open WIs, and block merge on policy violations when --required-check is set.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-458"]}}, "prev_hash": "21d8cc8e987af83c11d562cec0314eee8e6d843d79844eaf26c7fd146c5e4030", "hash": "f1890c657bd160684e1db72ef61aa030ae470be51de5b910f269d44db1131850", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 879, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-443", "record": {"id": "REQ-443", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "specsmith ps CLI must surface process and session state for all tracked agent runs", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-443", "version": 1, "title": "specsmith ps CLI must surface process and session state for all tracked agent runs", "description": "The specsmith ps command has no explicit REQ. It must list all tracked PIDs from .specsmith/pids/, report status (running/stopped/unknown) for each, and integrate with kill-session so process cleanup is auditable and idempotent.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-459"]}}, "prev_hash": "f1890c657bd160684e1db72ef61aa030ae470be51de5b910f269d44db1131850", "hash": "dc41f2a4033a9b5c6db978928720caf46e56d0a9dd446a5a5172388bc584ae1c", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 880, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-444", "record": {"id": "REQ-444", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Native Warp integration", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-444", "version": 1, "title": "Native Warp integration", "description": "specsmith provides a first-class Warp integration: a 'warp' integration adapter (specsmith integrate warp) that generates Warp-native artifacts (MCP governance server config, a Tab Config for a governed session, and a governance skill) so Warp's agent is governed by specsmith; and the 'specsmith run' REPL detects when it runs inside Warp (TERM_PROGRAM/WARP_*) and adapts its banner/ready frame accordingly.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-460"]}}, "prev_hash": "dc41f2a4033a9b5c6db978928720caf46e56d0a9dd446a5a5172388bc584ae1c", "hash": "d428dab449d71047f90497d7efb8ead806cc08ba9eb4cd530461f104765d2d0a", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 881, "ts": "2026-07-13T23:50:02Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-445", "record": {"id": "REQ-445", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "VRAM-aware local model recommendations", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-445", "version": 1, "title": "VRAM-aware local model recommendations", "description": "First-class Ollama model recommendation engine: a model catalog with approximate Q4 VRAM footprints and a recommend_models(vram_gb)/recommend_for_hardware() API that selects a role lineup (default/coding, fast scratch, harder pass/reasoning, general) keyed by the detected GPU VRAM tier, with per-model fit assessment (fits/tight/spills-to-RAM). Exposed via 'specsmith local-model recommend' (+ --json). Must not change existing detect_local_model/detect_local_models behavior.", "source": "docs/requirements/", "status": "planned", "test_ids": ["TEST-461"]}}, "prev_hash": "d428dab449d71047f90497d7efb8ead806cc08ba9eb4cd530461f104765d2d0a", "hash": "2d5df0aa8b4576b3a7b669cc00aa17ddfbd01843e424d045bac793265e7ba4ef", "recursion_depth": 0}
