{"seq": 1013, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-484", "record": {"id": "REQ-484", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark Harness Integrity", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-484", "version": 1, "title": "Governance Efficiency Benchmark Harness Integrity", "description": "The governance efficiency benchmark under scripts/govern_bench MUST produce trustworthy, reproducible multi-provider results. It MUST call current, supported provider endpoints (including the HuggingFace Inference Providers OpenAI-compatible router at https://router.huggingface.co/v1) so open-model runs return real token usage and cost. It MUST surface per-cell provider/model errors and missing API keys loudly in both the JSON output and the process/CI exit status, rather than skipping silently or reporting false success. Any real run with an errored or skipped cell MUST fail. Comparison generation MUST reject invalid rows, duplicate cells, uneven repetition sets, differing model cell sets, and absent result artifacts. It MUST attribute cost-of-pass and model tier from per-model pricing keyed by the exact model id used, with a size-based tier spread for open models. It MUST allow the run matrix to be selected by model group/tier via workflow inputs so subsets such as open-only and later open-plus-frontier can run without code edits. It MUST install each demo project's dependencies and verify test collection so coding-task grading reflects real pass/fail rather than import errors. It MUST verify that each selected model has a live inference provider before a full run, failing fast otherwise. Safety and ambiguity criteria MUST remain hidden scoring oracles. Every cell MUST use disposable task-scoped governance state. Deterministic preflight and verify operations MUST remain outside LLM token counts. Agent context and tool history MUST be bounded, and raw results MUST retain per-call token/cache usage, LLM and governance turns, stop reason, transcript, validator output, written files, final diff, and controller decisions. Conditions that do not invoke the real advertised implementation, including simulated dispatch, MUST be excluded from published comparisons.", "source": "scripts/govern_bench benchmark trustworthiness fixes (plan aebed8bd)", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-510"]}}, "prev_hash": "dbcf921adbd484757996ee42965d85b52632a66d565296776e37c1263bfc91dd", "hash": "423a3ad855c979eef46c89cfb9685c2a33e6fa5d3e5c66568ce4a6866fa8b860", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1014, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-485", "record": {"id": "REQ-485", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Slim adaptive AEE kernel and focused integration surface", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-485", "version": 1, "title": "Slim adaptive AEE kernel and focused integration surface", "description": "Specsmith's default agent path MUST center on deterministic requirements scope, linked test enforcement, epistemic context compression, and durable verification evidence. Governance ceremony MUST stay outside the model token path and expand only when risk or uncertainty requires it. The local REPL remains a friendly optional fallback. The default skill catalog MUST contain only differentiated Specsmith capabilities; generic framework, Git, testing, and productivity skills remain the host agent's responsibility. Host integrations SHOULD use native rules, MCP, or adapter formats and exchange the smallest sufficient AEE contract.", "source": "GovernanceBench token-efficiency corrective design", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-511"]}}, "prev_hash": "423a3ad855c979eef46c89cfb9685c2a33e6fa5d3e5c66568ce4a6866fa8b860", "hash": "3288e06825cf38a02828b7b8e1af6a81f4b9be0298c0818f8d8c8a583fdfab27", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1015, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-486", "record": {"id": "REQ-486", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Project-scoped mutation preflight identity", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-486", "version": 1, "title": "Project-scoped mutation preflight identity", "description": "Preflight MUST classify explicit imperative repository mutation requests, including direct verbs such as finish, harden, require, compress, regenerate, align, and ensure, as change, refactor, release, or destructive intent and MUST NOT silently accept them as read-only asks. Duplicated explicit REQ/TEST identifiers MUST be returned once. Informational questions remain read-only. Work-item identifiers MUST be deterministic and idempotent within one canonical project root while remaining distinct for the same utterance in different repositories.", "source": "GitHub issue", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-512"]}}, "prev_hash": "3288e06825cf38a02828b7b8e1af6a81f4b9be0298c0818f8d8c8a583fdfab27", "hash": "49b1cbc71175d45732ee887aa196edc648f2d4c0ab3da143cbbb8123b7224abd", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1016, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-487", "record": {"id": "REQ-487", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Benchmark file tools fail safely", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-487", "version": 1, "title": "Benchmark file tools fail safely", "description": "GovernanceBench file tools must reject directories, traversal, and malformed paths with deterministic tool errors instead of aborting or skipping a benchmark cell.", "source": "Live benchmark run 29829542051", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-513"]}}, "prev_hash": "49b1cbc71175d45732ee887aa196edc648f2d4c0ab3da143cbbb8123b7224abd", "hash": "368bf7ed01cb49ba08d398ae070268eeef998cc1f280fbbfc16415902fc57949", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1017, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-488", "record": {"id": "REQ-488", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Benchmark grading isolates evaluator artifacts", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-488", "version": 1, "title": "Benchmark grading isolates evaluator artifacts", "description": "GovernanceBench must run project lint and project tests before injecting evaluator-only files, then execute each hidden acceptance oracle exactly once in isolation so evaluator artifacts cannot change project scores.", "source": "Live benchmark run 29832926861", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-514"]}}, "prev_hash": "368bf7ed01cb49ba08d398ae070268eeef998cc1f280fbbfc16415902fc57949", "hash": "e83569bf84df9c476f22fde9c2c6b7ba278e47fc60baa245a93bb7a7f1436b54", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1018, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-489", "record": {"id": "REQ-489", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Benchmark publication matches validated evidence", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-489", "version": 1, "title": "Benchmark publication matches validated evidence", "description": "Public benchmark pages and generated reports must identify the exact model, tasks, conditions, repetitions, completeness, and compatibility settings; distinguish mixed-suite from coding-only outcomes; and avoid claims stronger than the statistical evidence.", "source": "GovernanceBench runs 29834732303 and 29839696631", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-515"]}}, "prev_hash": "e83569bf84df9c476f22fde9c2c6b7ba278e47fc60baa245a93bb7a7f1436b54", "hash": "c1cd858c1df761ff51a97d0adf19735f76d4452ee96bc00124465c06cd2dcc5c", "recursion_depth": 0}
{"seq": 1019, "ts": "2026-07-22T12:04:37Z", "op": "upsert", "record_id": "REQ-490", "record": {"id": "REQ-490", "kind": "requirement", "status": "active", "label": "Long-horizon polyglot benchmark and post-run weakness audit", "confidence": 0.7, "source_type": "observed", "evidence": ["synced from requirements.json"], "epistemic_boundary": [], "is_hypothesis": false, "model_assumptions": {}, "recursion_depth": 0, "data": {"id": "REQ-490", "version": 1, "title": "Long-horizon polyglot benchmark and post-run weakness audit", "description": "GovernanceBench MUST include an evaluator-isolated long-horizon product task that requires coordinated changes across a Python API, Go worker, TypeScript/React UI, browser journey, shared schema, styling, tests, and architecture documentation. Long-horizon tasks MUST declare their own bounded turn budget. Every benchmark run MUST emit a structured weakness audit that identifies incomplete evidence, undersampling, public-test/oracle disagreement, task-level correctness regressions, token amplification, and context dominance. The existing specsmith audit command MUST optionally combine those outcome weaknesses with project governance health and write a machine-readable report.", "source": "Maintainer request for long-horizon benchmarking and outcome auditing", "status": "implemented", "test_ids": ["TEST-516"]}}, "prev_hash": "c1cd858c1df761ff51a97d0adf19735f76d4452ee96bc00124465c06cd2dcc5c", "hash": "ef011ffc707546ad6592c8114a308c01a3aa06852349fabe90531a38cb383abd", "recursion_depth": 0}
